```java
class CarException extends Exception {
    public CarException(String message) {
        super(message);
    }
}

class Car {
    private String make;
    private String model;
    private int year;
    private double fuelEfficiency; // in miles per gallon
    private double distanceTravelled; // in miles

    public Car(String make, String model, int year, double fuelEfficiency) throws CarException {
        if (year < 1900 || year > java.util.Calendar.getInstance().get(java.util.Calendar.YEAR)) {
            throw new CarException("Year must be between 1900 and the current year.");
        }
        if (fuelEfficiency <= 0) {
            throw new CarException("Fuel efficiency must be a positive value.");
        }
        this.make = make;
        this.model = model;
        this.year = year;
        this.fuelEfficiency = fuelEfficiency;
        this.distanceTravelled = 0; // Initialize distance travelled to zero
    }

    public void accelerate() {
        System.out.println("The car is accelerating.");
    }

    public void decelerate() {
        System.out.println("The car is decelerating.");
    }

    public void refuel(double fuel) throws CarException {
        if (fuel <= 0) {
            throw new CarException("Refuel amount must be positive.");
        }
        System.out.println("Refueled " + fuel + " gallons.");
    }

    public double calculateFuelConsumption() throws CarException {
        if (distanceTravelled < 0) {
            throw new CarException("Distance travelled must not be negative.");
        }
        return distanceTravelled / fuelEfficiency; // Fuel consumed in gallons
    }

    public void setDistanceTravelled(double distance) throws CarException {
        if (distance < 0) {
            throw new CarException("Distance travelled must not be negative.");
        }
        this.distanceTravelled = distance;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try {
            Car myCar = new Car("Toyota", "Camry", 2020, 30);
            myCar.accelerate();
            myCar.setDistanceTravelled(150); // Set distance travelled

            double fuelConsumed = myCar.calculateFuelConsumption();
            System.out.println("Fuel consumed for 150 miles: " + fuelConsumed + " gallons");

            myCar.refuel(10);
            myCar.decelerate();
        } catch (CarException e) {
            System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}
```

### Explanation:
- **CarException Class**: A custom exception class that extends `Exception`, allowing us to throw specific error messages related to car attributes.
- **Car Class**: Contains the required attributes (`make`, `model`, `year`, `fuelEfficiency`, and `distanceTravelled`) and methods for acceleration, deceleration, refueling, and calculating fuel consumption.
- **Constructors**: The constructor checks for valid values of `year` and `fuelEfficiency`, throwing a `CarException` if they are invalid.
- **Main Method**: Demonstrates creating a `Car` object, accelerating, setting the distance travelled, calculating fuel consumption, and handling any thrown exceptions. This part of the code is wrapped in a try-catch block to manage exceptions gracefully.

Here's a complete Java implementation of the `Car` class with the specified attributes, methods, and custom exception handling:

```java
public class Car {
    private String make;
    private String model;
    private int year;
    private double fuelEfficiency; // in miles per gallon (mpg)
    private double distanceTravelled; // in miles
    private double speed; // in mph
    private double fuelLevel; // in gallons

    // Custom exception class
    public static class CarException extends Exception {
        public CarException(String message) {
            super(message);
        }
    }

    // Constructor with validation
    public Car(String make, String model, int year, double fuelEfficiency, double distanceTravelled) throws CarException {
        setMake(make);
        setModel(model);
        setYear(year);
        setFuelEfficiency(fuelEfficiency);
        setDistanceTravelled(distanceTravelled);
        this.speed = 0;
        this.fuelLevel = 0;
    }

    // Getters and setters with validation
    public String getMake() {
        return make;
    }

    public void setMake(String make) {
        this.make = make;
    }

    public String getModel() {
        return model;
    }

    public void setModel(String model) {
        this.model = model;
    }

    public int getYear() {
        return year;
    }

    public void setYear(int year) throws CarException {
        int currentYear = java.time.Year.now().getValue();
        if (year < 1900 || year > currentYear) {
            throw new CarException("Year must be between 1900 and " + currentYear);
        }
        this.year = year;
    }

    public double getFuelEfficiency() {
        return fuelEfficiency;
    }

    public void setFuelEfficiency(double fuelEfficiency) throws CarException {
        if (fuelEfficiency <= 0) {
            throw new CarException("Fuel efficiency must be a positive value");
        }
        this.fuelEfficiency = fuelEfficiency;
    }

    public double getDistanceTravelled() {
        return distanceTravelled;
    }

    public void setDistanceTravelled(double distanceTravelled) throws CarException {
        if (distanceTravelled < 0) {
            throw new CarException("Distance travelled cannot be negative");
        }
        this.distanceTravelled = distanceTravelled;
    }

    public double getSpeed() {
        return speed;
    }

    public double getFuelLevel() {
        return fuelLevel;
    }

    // Methods
    public void accelerate(double increment) {
        if (increment > 0) {
            speed += increment;
            System.out.println("Accelerating. Current speed: " + speed + " mph");
        }
    }

    public void decelerate(double decrement) {
        if (decrement > 0) {
            speed = Math.max(0, speed - decrement);
            System.out.println("Decelerating. Current speed: " + speed + " mph");
        }
    }

    public void refuel(double gallons) {
        if (gallons > 0) {
            fuelLevel += gallons;
            System.out.println("Refueled. Current fuel level: " + fuelLevel + " gallons");
        }
    }

    public double calculateFuelConsumption() {
        return distanceTravelled / fuelEfficiency;
    }

