```java
public class Statistics {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        float[] data = {3.3f, 5.6f, 7.8f, 5.4f, 9.9f};
        System.out.printf("Standard Deviation: %.2f%n", calculateStandardDeviation(data));
    }

    public static double calculateStandardDeviation(float[] data) {
        if (data == null || data.length == 0) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Data array must not be null or empty");
        }

        double sum = 0.0;
        double sumSquared = 0.0;
        int n = data.length;

        // Single loop to calculate sum and sum of squares
        for (float num : data) {
            sum += num;
            sumSquared += num * num;
        }

        // Calculate mean
        double mean = sum / n;

        // Calculate variance
        double variance = (sumSquared / n) - (mean * mean);

        // Return standard deviation
        return Math.sqrt(variance);
    }
}
```

### Explanation:

1. **Single Loop Efficiency**: The code calculates both the sum and the sum of squares in a single loop, which keeps the time complexity at O(n).

